  "epigraph": {
    "text": "I have fought the good fight, I have finished the \nrace, I have kept the faith.",
    "reference": "2 Timothy 4:7",
    "quote": "Success is the ability to go from one failure to another with no loss of enthusiasm.",
    "quoteAuthor": "Winston Churchill"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{Success is the ability to go from one failure to another with no loss of enthusiasm.}{Winston Churchill}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You now have four methods for solving quadratic equations: factoring, \nsquare roots, completing the square, and the quadratic formula. Each \nhas its strengths, and the skilled problem-solver knows when to use \neach."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts Summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Vocabulary Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Quadratic equation A. $b^2 - 4ac$",
        "Standard form B. $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$",
        "Zero Product Property C. One repeated solution",
        "Discriminant D. If $AB = 0$, then $A = 0$ or $B = 0$",
        "Double root E. Equation with highest power 2",
        "Completing the square F. Making a perfect square trinomial"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "*Answers: 1-E, 2-B, 3-D, 4-A, 5-C, 6-F*"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chapter Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Factoring (Section 9.1)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve by factoring."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 + 8x + 15 = 0$",
        "$x^2 - x - 30 = 0$",
        "$2x^2 - 9x + 4 = 0$",
        "$6x^2 + x - 2 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Square Root Method (Section 9.2)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 = 81$",
        "$3x^2 - 27 = 0$",
        "$(x - 4)^2 = 25$",
        "$(2x + 1)^2 = 16$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Completing the Square (Section 9.3)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve by completing the square."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 + 6x + 2 = 0$",
        "$x^2 - 10x + 21 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Quadratic Formula (Sections 9.4–9.5)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve using the quadratic formula."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 + 3x - 5 = 0$",
        "$2x^2 - 4x - 3 = 0$",
        "$x^2 + 4x + 6 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the discriminant and describe the solutions."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 + 6x + 9 = 0$",
        "$x^2 - 5x + 7 = 0$",
        "$3x^2 - 2x - 5 = 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Applications (Section 9.6)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A ball is thrown upward with height $h = -16t^2 + 32t + 48$. \nWhen does it hit the ground?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The product of two consecutive integers is 156. Find them."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Mixed Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve by any method."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^2 - 49 = 0$",
        "$x^2 + 5x = 14$",
        "$3x^2 + 4x - 1 = 0$",
        "$(x - 2)^2 = 18$"
      ]
    }
  ]
}